Category:Connecticut tornadoes
Category:Tornadoes of 2006

The Westchester Tornado was an F2 tornado that touched down in Rockland New York 

On July 12, a supercell thunderstorm developed over eastern New Jersey in association with a surface low-pressure area in southwestern Ontario. Daytime heating in the Tri-State Region led to moderate instability, a key factor in the development of showers and thunderstorms. With conditions favorable for the development of a tornado, the Storm Prediction Center issued a tornado watch was issued at 12:40 p.m. EDT (16:40 UTC). At around 12:05 p.m. EDT (16:05 UTC), a thunderstorm produced winds up to 60 mph (95 km/h) in Warren County, New Jersey, which snapped tree limbs and damaged power lines. A stronger thunderstorm developed around 1 p.m. EDT (17:00 UTC) and produced a funnel cloud near Carlstadt, New Jersey, no damage was associated with the funnel.



